{"title_page": "Ric Hassani", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                  = Ric Hassani\n| birth_name            = Ikechukwu Eric Ahiauzu\n| alias                 = Rico Slim\n| image                 = Ric Hassani at LOS.jpg\n| image_size            = \n| landscape             = \n| background            = solo_singer\n|caption                = Hassani performing at Lake of Stars in Malawi\n| birth_date            = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1989|01|06}}\n| birth_place           = [[Port Harcourt]], [[Rivers State]], Nigeria\n| genre                 = [[Soul music|Soul]], [[Reggae music|Reggae]], [[Pop music|Pop]] \n| occupation            = {{hlist|Singer|songwriter}}\n| website               = {{URL|richassani.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Ric Hassani''' (born '''Ikechukwu Eric Ahiauzu''') is a Nigerian singer, songwriter and musician.<ref name=\"guardian\">{{Cite news|url=https://guardian.ng/life/on-the-cover/africas-rising-star-ric-hassani/|title=Africa's Rising Star: Ric Hassani|newspaper=[[The Guardian (Nigeria)|The Guardian]]|date=December 20, 2016|accessdate=July 14, 2018}}</ref> Hassani was born on 6 January 1989, in [[Port Harcourt]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.naija.ng/1147833-ric-hassani-biography.html#1147833|title=Ric Hassani bio and interesting facts|last=Agu|first=Zain|work=Naija.ng - Nigeria news|date=February 14, 2018|accessdate=July 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\nHis love for fashion and personal grooming is not only shown in his music videos but is evident in his lifestyle. He regards his fashion as a touch of African and the gentleman style. He once said on an interview with Spice Tv that he should be one of the men , if not the man ,who first promoted wearing African fabrics (especially ankara fabric) in complete sense of a suit. \n\nRic Hassani is a brand and fashion influencer and models as a sponsored partnership with brands. His signature look or identity is his pair of spectacles neatly groomed beard with hand accessories. \n\n== Education ==\nHassani graduated from [[Covenant University]] in [[Nigeria]]. He attended the [[University of Surrey]], where he earned a master's degree in energy economics.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tribuneonlineng.com/105198/|title=Artiste of the week: Ric Hassani|newspaper=[[Nigerian Tribune]]|date=August 4, 2017|accessdate=July 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Musical career==\nHassani released his debut album ''The African Gentleman'' in 2016. He is said to have a dress style that is influenced by his self-acclaimed stance as a gentleman.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Emeka|last=Nwankwo|url=https://lifestyle.thecable.ng/ric-hassani-port-harcourt-gentleman/|title=FACE-TO-FACE: How the nerdy Port Harcourt boy \u2014 Ric Hassani \u2014 lost and found himself|work=[[TheCable]] Lifestyle|date=November 25, 2017|accessdate=July 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and Nominations ==\nHassani was nominated in three categories at the 2016 [[All Africa Music Awards]]: Best Artiste in African R&B and Soul, Video of the Year, and Most Promising Artiste.<ref>{{cite web |first=Abiola |last=Solanke |title=Wizkid, Tekno, Brymo lead regional nominees list |url=https://www.pulse.ng/buzz/afrima-2016-wizkid-tekno-brymo-lead-regional-nominees-list-id5416687.html |website=Pulse.ng |date=August 24, 2016 |accessdate=July 20, 2018}}</ref> He also received two nominations at [[The Headies 2016]], including Best Alternative Song for \"Gentleman\".<ref name=\"guardian\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailytrust.com.ng/news/weekend-mag/why-i-prefer-to-sing-love-songs-ric-hassani/208693.html|title=Why I prefer to sing love songs \u2013 Ric Hassani|last=Bivan|first=Nathaniel|date=August 5, 2017|website=[[Media Trust|The Daily Trust]]|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=July 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2018, the [[Falz]] and [[Olamide]]-assisted \"Believe\" won Best Collaboration at the Galaxy Music Awards.<ref>{{cite web |first=Gist |last=Always |title= GMA2018: Full list of winners at Galaxy Music Awards, facial reactions and more |url= https://gistalways.ng/gma2018-full-list-of-winners-at-galaxy-music-awards-facial-reactions-and-more |website=Gist Always |date=December 3, 2018 |accessdate=December 3, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n'''Studio albums'''\n*''The African Gentleman'' (2016)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hassani, Ric}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Singers from Port Harcourt]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from Rivers State]]\n[[Category:Covenant University alumni]]\n[[Category:21st-century Nigerian singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                  = Ric Hassani\n| birth_name            = Ikechukwu Eric Ahiauzu\n| alias                 = Rico Slim\n| image                 = Ric Hassani at LOS.jpg\n| image_size            = \n| landscape             = \n| background            = solo_singer\n|caption                = Hassani performing at Lake of Stars in Malawi\n| birth_date            = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1989|01|06}}\n| birth_place           = [[Port Harcourt]], [[Rivers State]], Nigeria\n| genre                 = [[Soul music|Soul]], [[Reggae music|Reggae]], [[Pop music|Pop]] \n| occupation            = {{hlist|Singer|songwriter}}\n| website               = {{URL|richassani.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Ric Hassani''' (born '''Ikechukwu Eric Ahiauzu''') is a Nigerian singer, songwriter and musician.<ref name=\"guardian\">{{Cite news|url=https://guardian.ng/life/on-the-cover/africas-rising-star-ric-hassani/|title=Africa's Rising Star: Ric Hassani|newspaper=[[The Guardian (Nigeria)|The Guardian]]|date=December 20, 2016|accessdate=July 14, 2018}}</ref> Hassani was born on 6 January 1989, in [[Port Harcourt]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.naija.ng/1147833-ric-hassani-biography.html#1147833|title=Ric Hassani bio and interesting facts|last=Agu|first=Zain|work=Naija.ng - Nigeria news|date=February 14, 2018|accessdate=July 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\nHas